Explanation:

We use a Map to store the cache with key-value pairs. When getting a value, we simply retrieve the pair from the map. When putting a value, we remove the existing key from the map, remove it from the cache, and then add the new pair to the map and cache. The time complexity is O(1) for both get and put operations, as we only perform constant operations on the map and cache. The space complexity is O(1) because we only use a constant amount of space for the map and cache. The energy implications are low because the operations are energy-efficient.

